SALESFORCE RELEASE NOTES
Provide Personalized Support to Customers with Summaries on Timeline

Configure Timeline to show summaries of events to your contact center agents (CCAs). The summaries provide the CCAs with a quick overview of events and enhance their understanding of past events.

Where: This change applies to Lightning Experience in clouds where Timeline is available.

Who: To use this feature, users need the Industry Service Excellence add-on license. You must turn on the Timeline Summary admin setting.

How: From Setup, on the Timeline page, create a Timeline and click Timeline Related Objects. On the Salesforce Platform Events tab, enter the details, select the field containing the summary, and then activate the Timeline.
